<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="53" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
In the protologue of 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus f., 1782" authorityName="Linnaeus f." authorityYear="1782" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Carolinea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Carolinea minor" order="Malvales" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Carolinea minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sims, J" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin du Jardin botanique National de Belgique" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" refId="B31" refString="Sims, J, 1811. Carolinea minor. Botanical Magazine 34: t. 1412." title="Carolinea minor. Botanical Magazine 34: t. 1412." year="1811">Sims (1811)</bibRefCitation>
states that he received this plant from &quot;Messrs. Loddiges and Sons, under the name of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bombacaceae" genus="Bombax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bombax" order="Malvales" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Bombax</taxonomicName>
Carolinoides
</emphasis>
, an appellation given it by Dr. 
<taxonomicName genus="Anderson" lsidName="Anderson" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="genus">Anderson</taxonomicName>
of the Botanic Garden at St. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Vincent’s.”">Vincent's.&quot;</normalizedToken>
Thus, original material that can be considered for a lectotype is either a cultivated specimen (or specimens) from Loddiges nursery in Hackney (now London) or the plate (t. 1412) illustrating 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus f., 1782" authorityName="Linnaeus f." authorityYear="1782" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Carolinea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Carolinea minor" order="Malvales" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Carolinea minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/3667210" author="Robyns, A" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin du Jardin botanique de l'Etat a Bruxelles" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" pagination="1 - 315" refId="B27" refString="Robyns, A, 1963. Essai de monographie du genre Bombax L. s.l. (Bombacaceae). Bulletin du Jardin botanique de l'Etat a Bruxelles 33: 1 - 315, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/3667210" title="Essai de monographie du genre Bombax L. s. l. (Bombacaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/3667210" volume="33" year="1963">Robyns (1963</bibRefCitation>
, p. 280) stated that the &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">holotypus</emphasis>
&quot; was at BM (&quot; 
<taxonomicName genus="Anderson" lsidName="Anderson" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Anderson</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">321</emphasis>
?) (BM)&quot;), but while it is clear that 
<taxonomicName genus="Anderson" lsidName="Anderson" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="genus">Anderson</taxonomicName>
conveyed seed to Loddiges, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sims’s">Sims's</normalizedToken>
description was not based on 
<taxonomicName genus="Anderson" lsidName="Anderson" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="genus">Anderson</taxonomicName>
's wild-collected herbarium material and such specimens are not original material. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Robyn’s">Robyn's</normalizedToken>
&quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">holotypus</emphasis>
&quot; cannot therefore be corrected to neotype (see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" author="Turland, NJ" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" refId="B40" refString="Turland, NJ, Wiersema, JH, Barrie, FR, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, DL, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Kusber, W-H, Li, D-Z, Marhold, K, May, TW, McNeill, J, Monro, AM, Prado, J, Price, MJ, Smith, GF [Eds], 2018. International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten. https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten." url="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" year="2018">Turland et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
; Art. 9.10).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/3667210" author="Robyns, A" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin du Jardin botanique de l'Etat a Bruxelles" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" pagination="1 - 315" refId="B27" refString="Robyns, A, 1963. Essai de monographie du genre Bombax L. s.l. (Bombacaceae). Bulletin du Jardin botanique de l'Etat a Bruxelles 33: 1 - 315, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/3667210" title="Essai de monographie du genre Bombax L. s. l. (Bombacaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/3667210" volume="33" year="1963">Robyns (1963</bibRefCitation>
, p. 284) effectively designated a lectotype for the name 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bombacaceae" genus="Pachira" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pachira nitida" order="Malvales" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nitida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Pachira nitida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
when he stated that a collection from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Caño">Cano</normalizedToken>
de Pimichin made by F.W.H.A. von Humboldt and A.J.A. Bonpland was the &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">holotypus</emphasis>
.&quot; The handwriting on the label of this specimen (P barcode 00679764) is that of Kunth (see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.15553/c2012v671a10" author="Stauffer, FW" journalOrPublisher="Candollea" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" pagination="75 - 130" refId="B36" refString="Stauffer, FW, Stauffer, J, Dorr, LJ, 2012. Bonpland and Humboldt specimens, field notes, and herbaria; new insights from a study of the monocotyledons collected in Venezuela. Candollea 67 (1): 75 - 130, DOI: https://doi.org/10.15553/c2012v671a10" title="Bonpland and Humboldt specimens, field notes, and herbaria; new insights from a study of the monocotyledons collected in Venezuela." url="https://doi.org/10.15553/c2012v671a10" volume="67" year="2012">Stauffer et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
) and the fragmentary nature of the flower agrees with statements in the protologue (here translated) that declare &quot;Only fragments available to us. A description of a flower from the label of Bonpland.&quot; The handwriting on the label of the isolectotype (P barcode 04694524) is that of Bonpland (see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.15553/c2012v671a10" author="Stauffer, FW" journalOrPublisher="Candollea" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" pagination="75 - 130" refId="B36" refString="Stauffer, FW, Stauffer, J, Dorr, LJ, 2012. Bonpland and Humboldt specimens, field notes, and herbaria; new insights from a study of the monocotyledons collected in Venezuela. Candollea 67 (1): 75 - 130, DOI: https://doi.org/10.15553/c2012v671a10" title="Bonpland and Humboldt specimens, field notes, and herbaria; new insights from a study of the monocotyledons collected in Venezuela." url="https://doi.org/10.15553/c2012v671a10" volume="67" year="2012">Stauffer et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
). This specimen was originally identified as 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus f., 1782" authorityName="Linnaeus f." authorityYear="1782" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Carolinea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Carolinea princeps" order="Malvales" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="princeps">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Carolinea princeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.f. (≡ 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. aquatica" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="aquatica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">P. aquatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), which also is noted in the protologue where 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. aquatica" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="aquatica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">P. aquatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is listed as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. nitida" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="nitida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">P. nitida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with doubt. The morphology of the leaves (leaflet shape, venation, and strongly raised midribs on abaxial surfaces) and of the flower (calyx shape and dimensions and stamen length) of the type of 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. nitida" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="nitida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">P. nitida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
matches that of the type of 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. minor" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">P. minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
